PROJECT: Recruitment Agency Static Website

This text document contains **all files** you need to publish a static website (HTML/CSS/JS) for a recruitment agency on GitHub Pages. Copy each file into your project folder (preserve folder names), commit to a repo, and enable GitHub Pages from that repo's settings.

---

FILE: README.md
```markdown
# Recruitment Agency Website

Static website for a recruitment agency. Contains pages: Home, About, Services, Contact.

## Features
- Separate pages (index.html, about.html, services.html, contact.html)
- Responsive layout (CSS only)
- Contact form with 4 options: Clients, Candidates, Student Service, General Enquiries
  - Form sends email via EmailJS (client-side). You must sign up at https://www.emailjs.com and replace placeholders in `js/main.js`.
  - Alternative instructions included for Formspree / Netlify Forms if you prefer serverless forms.

## How to use
1. Create a new GitHub repository and push the files in this project.
2. Replace placeholder company name, phone number, email addresses in the HTML and `js/main.js`.
3. If you want the contact form to email directly:
   - Option A (recommended, easy): Sign up for EmailJS, create a service & template, then update the keys in `js/main.js`.
   - Option B (Netlify Forms / Formspree): follow the commented instructions in `contact.html` and `js/main.js`.
4. Enable GitHub Pages: repo Settings → Pages → Source: `main` branch `/ (root)` or `/docs` folder. Your site will publish at `https://<username>.github.io/<repo>`.

## Files
- index.html
- about.html
- services.html
- contact.html
- css/style.css
- js/main.js
- assets/ (images placeholder)


## Notes about sending email from static sites
GitHub Pages only serves static files and cannot run server-side code. To send email directly from the form you must use a third-party service (EmailJS, Formspree, Netlify Forms) or a serverless function (AWS Lambda, Vercel, Netlify functions).

This project includes an EmailJS integration example (client-side). EmailJS requires creating an account and replacing `YOUR_USER_ID`, `YOUR_SERVICE_ID`, and `YOUR_TEMPLATE_ID` in `js/main.js`.
```

